Volunteer class
(a) every volunteer must have — id (int) – if possible system generated, name (string),
is_available (bool), DOB (Date)
(b) has suitable parameterized constructor
(c) has a method get_details to fetch volunteer details (ret type – string)
(d) has method validate_inputs (name doesn’t contain special chars, yearDOB < current
year, etc...) return type Volunteer
(e) is written populate_data() function (not less than 5 items)
(f) is written driven menu with options: Volunteer Registration, Volunteer Details, Quit
(g) when user select option Quit details of volunteers it is written to the file volunteers.ser
file.
//tested
